The problem with race mixing is that if there are too many interspecies couples the numbers of humans and anthros will start to decline. And it doesn't matter who you are or what you believe in, you have to admit that this is a bad thing. What if anthros used to be real, but they were bred out of existence by your ancestors? As long as they're healthy, hybrid children are not the problem, preserving both species is. I don't think that breeding out a species would be a factor though, it would depend on how genetically dominant they are compared to pure breeds, it also depends on how many interspecies couples there are. If hybrids were genetically dominant and/or there were too many interspecies couples, than adoption would be the best solution.
Hybrid children, however, are a much better alternative to not having children at all, if anthros and humans can't have children than it may be because God didn't intend us to be sexually compatible with each other, and that's a much bigger problem. Overall, I think hybrids are not ideal but they are a good compromise between both being realistic and having children.

tl,dr: healthy non-hybrid children ≥ healthy hybrid children >>> everything else
